# Architecture ADR Manual Maintenance Rule

Use `doc/architecture-adr-manual.qmd` as the source of truth for architecture decisions.

## End-of-step checklist (substantial architecture-impacting work)

- Determine whether the step introduced a new architectural decision or changed rationale/trade-offs of an existing one.
- If yes, add or update ADR entry in `doc/architecture-adr-manual.qmd` in the same step.
- Keep ADR status, date, decision, and implication explicit.
- If no ADR impact exists, explicitly confirm that no ADR update is required.

## Documentation discipline

- Keep ADR entries concise and additive; avoid rewriting history silently.
